d Koninkrijk","Forneyson Castle, Devon, England":"Castle Hill, Devon, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Musbury, Devon, England":"Musbury, Devon, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1327–1400":"1327–1400","1292–1327":"1292–1327","1312–Male":"1312–Deceased","1315–1373":"1315–1373","1340–1440":"1340–1440","1358–Female":"1358–Deceased","1360–1458":"1360–1458","1280–1332":"1280–1332","1270–1365":"1270–1365","1440":"1440","1340":"1340","1373":"1373","1360":"1360","1270":"1270","1292":"1292","1280":"1280","1327":"1327","1458":"1458","1315":"1315","1358":"1358","1400":"1400","1312":"1312","1332":"1332","about 1358":"about 1358","1365":"1365","Mar 1365":"March 1365","Clyst Fomison, Devon, England":"Sowton, Devon, England","Westho Parish, Devon, England":"Devon, England, United Kingdom","Forneyson Castle, Devon, England":"Castle Hill, Devon, England, United Kingdom","Musbury, Devon, England":"Musbury, Devon, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Ashe","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Irish and English: variant of   Ash   1, found mainly in Ireland.","Americanized form (translation into English) of French   Dufresne  , a variant of   Ash   2.","History: This is the name of a prominent NC family; John Baptist Ashe settled in NC before 1720. It is not known where he came from: his personal name suggests that he may have been of French extraction, perhaps originally named Jean-Baptiste Dufresne."],"variants":[{"name":"Ash","meanings":["English: from Middle English <i>asche</i> ‘ash tree’ (Old English <i>æsc</i>), hence a topographic name for someone living by an ash tree or a habitational name from any of the many places in southern and central England named with this word (Derbyshire, Dorset, Hampshire, Herefordshire, Kent, Surrey, Shropshire, Somerset, and elsewhere).","Americanized form of German   Asch   and   Esch  , the latter ultimately also of Swiss German origin (see   Oesch  ).","Americanized form (translation into English) of French   Dufresne  , with the same meaning as 1 above."]}]},{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Esse","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Scandinavian Erik.","Norwegian: habitational name from the farmstead Ese in Sogn of unexplained etymology, or Esse in Telemark, named with Old Norse <i>æsin</i> ‘hill’ + <i>-e</i> from <i>vin</i> ‘meadow’.","German: variant of   Ess  , or a topographic name from the river name Esse in Hesse."],"variants":[{"name":"Ess","meanings":["North German: topographic name for someone living on or owning land that was waterlogged or partly surrounded by water, from Middle Low German <i>es</i> ‘swamp, water’.","Swiss German: from the topographic name <i>Ess</i> ‘grazing area, pasture’.","Swiss German: from a vernacular short form of the personal name   Oswald  ."]}]},{"name":"Henry","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["A perennially popular given name, of Continental Germanic origin, from <i>haim</i> ‘home’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power, ruler’. It was an Old French name, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Henry Ashe de Esse was born in 1327, in Musbury, Devon, England, United Kingdom, his father, Oliver Ashe de Esse, was 47 and his mother, Lady Emma D'Esse Cruys, was 57. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Margery Fornyson. He died in 1400, in Castle Hill, Devon, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 73."},"et":{"1327–1400":"1327–1400","1292–1327":"1292–1327","1312–Male":"1312–Surnud","1315–1373":"1315–1373","1340–1440":"1340–1440","1358–Female":"1358–Surnud","1360–1458":"1360–1458","1280–1332":"1280–1332","1270–1365":"1270–1365","1440":"1440","1340":"1340","1373":"1373","1360":"1360","1270":"1270","1292":"1292","1280":"1280","1327":"1327","1458":"1458","1315":"1315","1358":"1358","1400":"1400","1312":"1312","1332":"1332","about 1358":"umbes 1358","1365":"1365","Mar 1365":"märts 1365","Clyst Fomison, Devon, England":"Sowton, Devon, England","Westho Parish, Devon, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Forneyson Castle, Devon, England":"Castle Hill, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Musbury, Devon, England":"Musbury, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1327–1400":"1327–1400","1292–1327":"1292–1327","1312–Male":"1312–Kuollut","1315–1373":"1315–1373","1340–1440":"1340–1440","1358–Female":"1358–Kuollut","1360–1458":"1360–1458","1280–1332":"1280–1332","1270–1365":"1270–1365","1440":"1440","1340":"1340","1373":"1373","1360":"1360","1270":"1270","1292":"1292","1280":"1280","1327":"1327","1458":"1458","1315":"1315","1358":"1358","1400":"1400","1312":"1312","1332":"1332","about 1358":"noin 1358","1365":"1365","Mar 1365":"maaliskuu 1365","Clyst Fomison, Devon, England":"Sowton, Devon, England","Westho Parish, Devon, England":"Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Forneyson Castle, Devon, England":"Castle Hill, De